nemacs-next TUI frontend
========================

Launch from the repository root:

  apps/nemacs-next/frontends/tui/nemacs-next-tui

The launcher starts one persistent NeLisp session with the existing bootstrap
REPL, switches an interactive terminal to raw mode, restores the terminal on
exit, and exits cleanly on stdin EOF for scripted smokes.

Key map
-------

  Printable characters   insert text
  RET                    insert newline
  DEL / Backspace        delete backward
  Left / C-b             backward-char
  Right / C-f            forward-char
  Down / C-n             next-line
  Up / C-p               previous-line
  C-/                    undo
  C-x C-f                find-file prompt
  C-x C-s                save-buffer
  F10 / M-`              focus toolbar
  Toolbar Left / Right   move current toolbar item
  Toolbar RET            invoke current toolbar item
  Toolbar ESC            leave toolbar focus
  C-x C-c                quit

The toolbar is rendered on the top row from session protocol data.  The
default item order follows vendor `tool-bar-setup`: New File, Open, Dired,
Close, Save, Undo, Cut, Copy, Paste, Search, with separators preserved.

The v2 renderer consumes the session frame snapshot directly. Viewport rows may
include face runs sourced from buffer text properties, and the frontend maps the
initial face set to ANSI colors:

  org-level-1              bright blue, bold
  org-level-2              bright cyan, bold
  org-level-3              green, bold
  org-level-4              yellow, bold
  bold                     bold
  font-lock-comment-face   gray
  font-lock-string-face    green
  default                  reset

Resolved foreground names from the face registry override that table for the
small named-color set currently supported by the TUI.

Interactive draws compare rendered rows with the previous frame and rewrite
only changed rows. Cursor-only movement emits only cursor positioning. In a
terminal, IME composition remains owned by the terminal; the frontend reads a
complete UTF-8 byte sequence before sending text input to the session.

Smoke
-----

  apps/nemacs-next/frontends/tui/smoke.sh

The smoke pipes deterministic byte sequences through the frontend. It keeps the
find-file/edit/delete/quit path, invokes toolbar Save, invokes toolbar Open and
asserts the prompt, checks that every default toolbar label rendered, adds
Japanese UTF-8 insertion, asserts ANSI color output for an Org heading face run,
and checks that a cursor-only move is much smaller than a full-frame redraw.
